  "explanation": "Expand around center: for each character (and space between), expand outward as long as it forms a palindrome. Track the longest one found.",
  "answer": "def longestPalindrome(s):\n    if not s: return \"\"\n    def expand(l, r):\n        while l >= 0 and r < len(s) and s[l] == s[r]: l -= 1; r += 1\n        return s[l+1:r]\n    res = \"\"\n    for i in range(len(s)):\n        p1 = expand(i, i)\n        if len(p1) > len(res): res = p1\n        p2 = expand(i, i+1)\n        if len(p2) > len(res): res = p2\n    return res",
